verbose_text: The gold catalyst in absence of cage and base is completely inactive for the cycloisomerization of 1 (entry 1), which is different from what we observed previously for 4-pentynoic acid,15 highlighting the difference in reactivity of the substrates.18 When the gold catalyst was applied in the presence of sphere or with a catalytic amount of base, the formation of product 3 was observed, although only in low yields (entries 2 and 4).
